This paper proposes a framework for the analysis and optimization of air-to-ground (A2G) communication systems using unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs). The paper focuses on the wireless network aspects of the A2G system, which suggests that it belongs to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also incorporates path loss exponent and small-scale fading, which are topics covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper proposes a cooperative communication network, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of UAVs as aerial base stations for future networks, which suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of the network for multiple destinations, which could fall under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
